/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Service-Worker-Allowed: /
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: interest-cohort=(), browsing-topics=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' blob: https://assets.lemonsqueezy.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob: https:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://models.wyreup.com; worker-src 'self' blob:; manifest-src 'self'; media-src 'self' blob: data:; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; frame-src https://app.lemonsqueezy.com; form-action 'self'

# The two Cross-Origin-* headers above enable SharedArrayBuffer, which is
# required by ffmpeg.wasm (multi-threaded WASM) and Transformers.js (some
# multi-threaded model inference paths). Without them, `SharedArrayBuffer is
# not defined` at runtime.
#
# `credentialless` was chosen over `require-corp` historically because
# AI/media tools fetched models/wasm from third-party CDNs. As of
# 2026-05-15 every model fetch routes through models.wyreup.com (a
# first-party Cloudflare Worker — see `packages/worker-models/`), so
# `require-corp` would now work if we want it. Keeping `credentialless`
# for the moment because there's no concrete benefit to flipping it;
# revisit if a future tool needs `require-corp`-only behavior.
#
# Browser support: Chrome 96+, Edge 96+, Firefox 123+, Safari 17.4+ — ~95%
# of sessions. Older browsers fall through to require-corp semantics which
# would break fetches, so we degrade gracefully for those users (the tool
# itself shows an error; the site still loads).
#
# Service-Worker-Allowed: / lets the SW (served from /sw.js) intercept
# requests under the entire origin, not just /sw.js's own directory. This
# is the default scope for a root-served SW, but spelling it out keeps the
# behavior stable if someone moves the file later.
#
# CSP notes:
#   - 'unsafe-inline' is needed for the BaseLayout's inline scripts
#     (pre-paint reservation, PWA-mode redirect) and for Astro's scoped
#     <style> tags. Could be tightened with nonce-based CSP later; not
#     worth the build-step complexity until we have a reason.
#   - 'wasm-unsafe-eval' allows WebAssembly compilation — required by
#     ffmpeg.wasm, ONNX Runtime, transformers.js. The non-eval
#     alternative would require shipping pre-compiled module bytes,
#     which is incompatible with our model CDN.
#   - blob: in script-src is REQUIRED by transformers.js v4 / onnxruntime-web,
#     which bootstrap the ORT wasm backend by creating a Blob of the runtime
#     .mjs and dynamically import()-ing it (createObjectURL → import(blob:)).
#     Module imports are governed by script-src, so without blob: the import
#     is refused with "Failed to fetch dynamically imported module: blob:…"
#     and ORT reports "no available backend found". (worker-src already has
#     blob:; the v3→v4 bump moved this load onto the main thread.) Do not
#     remove without confirming transcribe/ML tools still load in a browser.
#   - connect-src is intentionally tight: 'self' for /api/* + same-origin
#     fetches, models.wyreup.com for model/WASM downloads. No third-party
#     hosts. Model providers (Workers AI, Replicate, ZeptoMail) are all
#     called server-side from Pages Functions; the browser never reaches
#     them directly.
#   - frame-ancestors 'none' + X-Frame-Options: DENY blocks clickjacking
#     (admin /grant click hijacking in particular).
#   - object-src 'none' kills <embed>/<object> Flash/PDF plugin attacks.

# PWA: ensure manifest and service worker updates roll out fast. Browsers
# cache these aggressively otherwise; users would stay on a stale SW for
# days after a deploy.
/manifest.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  Content-Type: application/manifest+json; charset=utf-8

/sw.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  Service-Worker-Allowed: /

/registerSW.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
